%BOM---------------------
Date:7/30/2011 2:38:47 AM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
OMG, you just summed it? OMG. I am lost for words.

OK, go and learn math and stat. When you understand how to calculate return, we
can talk again. Because right now you are just embarrassing yourself. I hope
you're not a math or economics major...

For anyone who is too lazy or math challenged to perform calculations, badi_'s
real return on the given portfolio is... 1.7%

Paste his numbers to Excel. For each number calculate =(100+CellNo)*0.01 <-
this is what $1 invested into the stock would turn into at the end of holding
period. Sum the resulting numbers <- this is the value of portfolio at the end
of holding period. Divide the value by 209 <- this is the value of the
portfolio in the beginning. Voila.

So much for "Black Swans"...
